#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.0"
msgid "72. Vilekhanasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.72\">Monks’ Confession 72: the training rule on "
"annoyance</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.72.1\""
">Bu-Pc.72.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.40\">BD.3.40</a><a class"
"=\"wt-pa\">1318</a>At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the "
"Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ anekapariyāyena vinayakathaṃ "
"katheti, vinayassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, vinayapariyattiyā vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, ādissa "
"ādissa āyasmato upālissa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati."
msgstr ""
"At that time the Master gave many talks about the monastic law, spoke in "
"praise of the monastic law and of learning the monastic law, and he "
"repeatedly praised Venerable Upāli."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.3"
msgid "Bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—"
msgstr "When the monks heard this, they thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.4"
msgid ""
"“bhagavā kho anekapariyāyena vinayakathaṃ katheti, vinayassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, "
"vinayapariyattiyā vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, ādissa ādissa āyasmato upālissa vaṇṇaṃ "
"bhāsati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.5"
msgid ""
"Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, āyasmato upālissa santike vinayaṃ pariyāpuṇāmā”ti, te ca "
"bahū bhikkhū therā ca navā ca majjhimā ca āyasmato upālissa santike vinayaṃ "
"pariyāpuṇanti."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, let’s learn the monastic law from Venerable Upāli.” And many "
"monks, both senior and junior, as well as those of middle standing, learned "
"the monastic law from Upāli.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-vp-pli4.143
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.6"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1319</a>The monks from the group of six <a class=\"pts-"
"vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.143\">Vin.4.143</a> thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.7"
msgid ""
"“etarahi kho, āvuso, bahū bhikkhū therā ca navā ca majjhimā ca āyasmato "
"upālissa santike vinayaṃ pariyāpuṇanti."
msgstr "“If these monks become well-versed in the monastic law,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.8"
msgid ""
"Sace ime vinaye pakataññuno bhavissanti amhe yenicchakaṃ yadicchakaṃ "
"yāvadicchakaṃ ākaḍḍhissanti parikaḍḍhissanti."
msgstr ""
"they’ll push us around and pull us about as they like, wherever they like, "
"to whatever extent they like."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.9"
msgid "Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, vinayaṃ vivaṇṇemā”ti."
msgstr "So let’s disparage the monastic law.” </p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.10"
msgid "Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadanti—"
msgstr "<p>And they approached the other monks and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.11"
msgid ""
"“kiṃ panimehi khuddānukhuddakehi sikkhāpadehi uddiṭṭhehi, yāvadeva "
"kukkuccāya vihesāya vilekhāya saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“What’s the point of reciting these <a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.3.41\""
">BD.3.41</a> minor and insignificant training rules, when they just lead to "
"annoyance, anxiety, and oppression?”</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.12"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1320</a>The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.13"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.14"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū vinayaṃ vivaṇṇessantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six disparage the monastic law?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.15"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, vinayaṃ vivaṇṇethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.16"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.17"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.18"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, vinayaṃ vivaṇṇessatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you disparage the monastic law?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.19"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.20"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc4
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:1.1.21"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu pātimokkhe uddissamāne evaṃ vadeyya—‘kiṃ panimehi "
"khuddānukhuddakehi sikkhāpadehi uddiṭṭhehi, yāvadeva kukkuccāya vihesāya "
"vilekhāya saṃvattantī’ti, sikkhāpadavivaṇṇake pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2><p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1321</a>‘When the monastic code is being recited, if a monk says, “What’s "
"the point of reciting these minor and insignificant training rules, when "
"they just lead to annoyance, anxiety, and oppression?” then in disparaging "
"the training rules, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc5
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.72.2\"></a><a "
"class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.72.2.1\">Bu-Pc.72.2.1</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1322</a><term>A</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>…"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr ""
"The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through "
"a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this "
"case.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.1.6"
msgid "Pātimokkhe uddissamāneti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1323</a><term>When the monastic code is being "
"recited</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.1.7"
msgid "uddisante vā uddisāpente vā sajjhāyaṃ vā karonte."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>when reciting it, when getting it recited, or when practicing "
"it.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.1.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vadeyyāti—"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1324</a><term>Says</term>:"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.1.9"
msgid ""
"“kiṃ panimehi khuddānukhuddakehi sikkhāpadehi uddiṭṭhehi, yāvadeva "
"kukkuccāya vihesāya vilekhāya saṃvattantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>“What’s the point of reciting these minor and insignificant training "
"rules, when they just lead to annoyance, anxiety, and oppression?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.1.10"
msgid ""
"“Ye imaṃ pariyāpuṇanti tesaṃ kukkuccaṃ hoti, vihesā hoti, vilekhā hoti, ye "
"imaṃ na pariyāpuṇanti tesaṃ kukkuccaṃ na hoti vihesā na hoti vilekhā na hoti."
msgstr ""
"If he disparages the monastic law to one who is fully ordained, saying, “"
"Those who learn this will be anxious/will feel oppressed/<a class=\"pts-vp-"
"en\" id=\"BD.3.42\">BD.3.42</a>will be annoyed, but those who don’t learn "
"this will not be anxious/will not feel oppressed/will not be annoyed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.1.11"
msgid ""
"Anuddiṭṭhaṃ idaṃ varaṃ, anuggahitaṃ idaṃ varaṃ, apariyāpuṭaṃ idaṃ varaṃ, "
"adhāritaṃ idaṃ varaṃ, vinayo vā antaradhāyatu, ime vā bhikkhū appakataññuno "
"hontū”ti upasampannassa vinayaṃ vivaṇṇeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"It’s better left unrecited/it’s better left unlearned/it’s better left "
"unstudied/it’s better left unmastered. Let the monastic law disappear, or "
"let these monks remain ignorant,” then he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.2.1"
msgid "Upasampanne upasampannasaññī vinayaṃ vivaṇṇeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.72.2.2\""
">Bu-Pc.72.2.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1325</a>If he disparages the monastic "
"law to one who is fully ordained, and he perceives them as fully ordained, "
"he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.2.2"
msgid "Upasampanne vematiko vinayaṃ vivaṇṇeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he disparages the monastic law to one who is fully ordained, but he is "
"unsure if they are, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.2.3"
msgid "Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī vinayaṃ vivaṇṇeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he disparages the monastic law to one who is fully ordained, but he does "
"not perceive them as fully ordained, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9, pts-vp-pli4.144
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.2.4"
msgid "Aññaṃ dhammaṃ vivaṇṇeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1326</a>If he disparages some other rule, he commits "
"an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.2.5"
msgid ""
"Anupasampannassa vinayaṃ vā aññaṃ vā dhammaṃ vivaṇṇeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he disparages the monastic law or some other rule to one who is not fully "
"ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.2.6"
msgid "Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p>If it is to one who is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as fully "
"ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.2.7"
msgid "Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is to one who is not fully ordained, <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4."
"144\">Vin.4.144</a> but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.2.8"
msgid "Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is to one who is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as "
"fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2><p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.72.2."
"3\">Bu-Pc.72.2.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1327</a>There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.3.2"
msgid ""
"na vivaṇṇetukāmo, “iṅgha tvaṃ suttante vā gāthāyo vā abhidhammaṃ vā "
"pariyāpuṇassu, pacchā vinayaṃ pariyāpuṇissasī”ti bhaṇati, ummattakassa, "
"ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if, not desiring to disparage, he says, “Listen, learn discourses/verses/"
"philosophy, and later you can learn the monastic law;” if he is insane; if "
"he is the first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc72:2.3.3"
msgid "Vilekhanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<hr><p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1328</a>The second rule, the "
"training rule on annoyance, is finished.</p>"
